Install the WebSocket package
bashcd your-project-root
npm install ws

PHASE 3 — USB/ADB Cable Option
If you want phones connected via USB cable instead of Wi-Fi:
bash# On your laptop, with phone USB-connected and USB debugging ON:
adb reverse tcp:5000 tcp:5000

# Now on the phone in Termux, use localhost:
python agent.py --role cctv --mode malicious --server http://localhost:5000

Enable USB debugging: Settings → Developer Options → USB Debugging. Run adb devices to verify the phone is recognized.


python agent.py --role cctv --mode malicious --server https://your-backend.onrender.com
```

---

## Quick Start Checklist
```
[ ] 1. Find laptop IP (ipconfig / ip a)
[ ] 2. Start your backend: node api/server.js
[ ] 3. Open port 5000 in firewall if needed
[ ] 4. Copy agent.py to each phone via Termux:
        curl -O http://YOUR_IP:8080/agent.py  (serve with: python -m http.server 8080)
[ ] 5. Run agent on Phone A (CCTV)
[ ] 6. Run agent on Phone B (Access Controller)
[ ] 7. Run agent on Phone C (Router)
[ ] 8. Open dashboard — devices appear in real time
[ ] 9. Click mode buttons to toggle malicious/normal
[ ] 10. For USB: adb reverse tcp:5000 tcp:5000 first